  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Edmonia Lewis is distressed because no one has written her about her group of sculptures, &quot;Forever free.&quot; She wants to know what has become of it and if Mr. [Samuel Edmund?] Sewall has the money for it yet, as she is in great financial need. Lewis writes: &quot;What little money I had I put all in that work with my heart.&quot; She requests that Mrs. Chapman see Mr. Sewall and ask him if he has been paid the $800 and to send her the money.</subfield>
